  <abstract>In this letter John Roller, HQ Co., 115th FA, writes to his brother Alvin that he had a good Christmas Day and holiday dinner. His presents included cigarettes and a sack of tobacco. Nashville ladies sent preserves and jellies. He advises his brother "-don't join the infantry." John would rather be in the regular army than the National Guard. "Old santa dident bring any thing here. Most all the boys got boxes from home." The letter is written on YMCA stationery.</abstract>
